<p><br/>Another Mountain Lion adjustment <a href="http://www.charlieegan3.com/2013/02/terminal-at-folder.html" target="_blank">post</a> - <b>Disable Notifications Center</b> (Fully<i>).</i><br/><br/>Run:<br/></p><blockquote class="tr_bq"><i>launchctl unload -w /System/Library/LaunchAgents/com.apple.notificationcenterui.plist</i></blockquote>from any Terminal window. This tells OSX that you don&rsquo;t want to run the daemon in future.<br/><br/>Then run:<br/><blockquote class="tr_bq"><i>killall NotificationCenter</i></blockquote>to stop the process that is currently running.<br/><br/>Almost done, the final step is to head to <i>System Preferences &gt; Trackpad &gt; More Gestures</i>. Then uncheck the &lsquo;Notification Center&rsquo; gesture.<br/><br/><div>To put the somewhat useless feature back just run:</div><blockquote class="tr_bq"><i>launchctl <b>load </b>-w /System/Library/LaunchAgents/com.apple.notificationcenterui.plist</i></blockquote> <b>-charlie out-</b>
